FEATURES
========

- DIC with subpixel resolution (bilinear, bicubic or biquintic interpolations)
- Particle Image Tracking (specific solutions to avoid loosing any particle)
- synthetic image generation (Perlin noise)
- correction of distortion (and solutions for the correction of parallax)
- subpixel positionning of disc centers
- Pattern characterisation


THIRD PARTY LIBRARIES (MANDATORY)
=================================
Tracker uses Magick++ and libRaw as third party library.
To install Magick++, simply install ImageMagick with the solution of your choice. This way, Magick++ will be installed with all re required tools.
To install libRaw, unpack the sources provided in the folder 'ThirdParty'. The compilation procedure is a simple './configure' followed by 'sudo make install'. 

COMPILATION
===========
It is as simple as a 'make' in the folder 'src' (provided that the third party libraries are correctly installed)


